docs/ is the project's documentation of record — design history, current status, and forward-looking specs for a Rust agentic-coding system (ctx-* CLI suite, context-tree mechanism, and a meal-planner reference project). Code and prompts elsewhere implement what's decided here; nothing here is executable.

The six files form a layered record with a specific reading order for "why is X this way": SPEC.md is the frozen, current-revision (rev 4) contract; STATUS.md is the living "what's true now" pointer into it and into ADR numbers; DECISIONS.md is the append-only rationale log that SPEC.md and STATUS.md both cite by ADR number rather than restate; UNIMPLEMENTED.md is the backlog cross-referencing SPEC.md's rev-2 contracts and DYLINT_RULES.md's undone rules; SANDBOX.md and DYLINT_RULES.md are narrower design docs — one retired, one not-yet-built. An editor changing behavior should update SPEC.md (if the contract changes) or STATUS.md (if only current-state changes), then add an ADR in DECISIONS.md rather than editing old ADR text, then check UNIMPLEMENTED.md's status markers against actual crate state.

Cross-file coupling to watch: SPEC.md's rollup/leaf line-budget numbers must stay identical to prompts/summarizer-rollup.md — a change to one without the other breaks the documented invariant. SPEC.md rev 4 supersedes its own body prose in the "Access protocol" section; readers must apply the revision paragraph over the literal old text rather than treat the file as internally consistent. SANDBOX.md is retired per ADR-035/040/041 but still cross-referenced by SPEC.md Layer 2 and UNIMPLEMENTED.md, both of which have themselves moved past it — none of the three should be read as the sole current truth in isolation. DYLINT_RULES.md's rule 1 and rule 4 overlap live mechanical checks in scripts/ (rationale_check.py, cycle_check.sh) and are meant to supersede them, not duplicate them, once built.

No intent.md exists for this directory.